<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="351" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,402,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Description</emphasis>
. Specimens with L10= 
<quantity box="[605,721,403,429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.35" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" unit="mm" value="6.35" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="3.7">3.7–9 mm</quantity>
, W10= 
<quantity box="[809,947,403,429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" unit="mm" value="1.45" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="0.6">0.6–2.3 mm</quantity>
. Prostomium entire. Median antenna reaching from second peristomial ring to middle of the second chaetiger; lateral antennae reaching from second peristomial ring to first chaetiger; palps reaching from first to second peristomial ring. Palpostyles and ceratostyles without peduncle. Eyes present. Maxillary formula: 
<collectingRegion box="[645,689,511,537]" country="Japan" name="Mie" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">MII</collectingRegion>
6–8+7–9, MIII 6–8, MIV 5–7+9–10 (
<figureCitation box="[1118,1239,510,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1125,1149]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,417,1102]" captionTargetId="figure-146@16.[151,1437,417,1102]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 6. Moulting of Paucibranchia bellii (Audouin &amp; Milne-Edwards, 1833) MNHN-AZ779,. A) Anterior region of the body, dorsal view; B) New generation of maxillae, dorsal view; C) Moulting of maxillae. Abbreviations: MI-V: maxillae from I to V, MC: maxillary carrier. Scale bars: A, 1.1 mm; B–C,0.7 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683256" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683256/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1118,1239,510,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Fig. 6A–C</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). MI length from 
<quantity box="[151,238,546,573]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
to 
<quantity box="[274,363,547,573]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
, maxillary carriers’ length from 
<quantity box="[728,828,546,573]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" unit="mm" value="0.35">0.35 mm</quantity>
to 
<quantity box="[865,953,547,573]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
, closing system length from 
<quantity box="[1278,1365,547,573]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
to 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[211,255,583,609]" country="Japan" name="Mie" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">MII</collectingRegion>
length from 
<quantity box="[406,508,582,609]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" unit="mm" value="0.55">0.55 mm</quantity>
to 
<quantity box="[548,638,583,609]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
, opening cavity length from 
<quantity box="[972,1060,583,609]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
to 
<quantity box="[1100,1167,583,609]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[1185,1308,582,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1125,1149]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,417,1102]" captionTargetId="figure-146@16.[151,1437,417,1102]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 6. Moulting of Paucibranchia bellii (Audouin &amp; Milne-Edwards, 1833) MNHN-AZ779,. A) Anterior region of the body, dorsal view; B) New generation of maxillae, dorsal view; C) Moulting of maxillae. Abbreviations: MI-V: maxillae from I to V, MC: maxillary carrier. Scale bars: A, 1.1 mm; B–C,0.7 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683256" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683256/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1185,1308,582,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Fig. 6A–C</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Pectinate branchiae starting from chaetigers 10–15 to chaetigers 22–43. The maximum number of branchial filaments from 9 to 22. Dorsal cirri conical, in median-posterior region 1.2 times longer than pre-branchial chaetigers. Prechaetal lobe as a transverse fold in all chaetigers. Chaetal lobe rounded in the anterior region, triangular in media-posterior parapodia. Postchaetal lobe tongue-shaped in pre-branchial chaetigers, conical in branchial chaetigers, inconspicuous in median-posterior chaetigers; well-developed in first 32–72 chaetigers. Ventral cirri digitiform in first chaetigers and posterior region; with a small swollen base from chaetigers 4–5 to chaetigers 37–78. Aciculae blunt, dark in the anterior region, amber in median-posterior parapodia. Limbate chaetae of two sizes in same chaetiger. Two 
<typeStatus box="[1347,1406,835,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">types</typeStatus>
of pectinate chaetae: (1) in anterior chaetigers, 1–2 pectinate isodont narrow chaetae with 4–5 long and slender teeth, with oblique distal edge; (2) in median-posterior chaetigers, 4–5 pectinate isodont narrow chaetae with 10–13 short and slender teeth, with transverse distal edge. Compound spinigers present in first 23–53 chaetigers. Compound falcigers present in all parapodia, with blades of two lengths in anterior chaetigers, one length in median-posterior chaetigers. Subacicular hooks bidentate, amber, starting in chaetigers 24–38, with one or two hooks per chaetiger.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,875,1050,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1329]" box="[199,875,1050,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1050,1076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Distribution</emphasis>
. English Channel, Western Mediterranean Sea.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="351" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1087,1113]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Remarks</emphasis>
. The species was recently redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Molina-Acevedo, I. C." box="[803,1081,1087,1113]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" pagination="1 - 125" refId="ref14193" refString="Molina-Acevedo, I. C. (2018) Morphological revision of the Subgroup 1 Fauchald, 1970 of Marphysa de Quatrefages, 1865 (Eunicidae: Polychaeta). Zootaxa, 4480 (1), 1 - 125. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4480.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Molina-Acevedo (2018)</bibRefCitation>
. For many years, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MNHN-AZ" baseAuthorityName="Audouin &amp; Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1294,1383,1087,1113]" class="Polychaeta" family="Eunicidae" genus="Paucibranchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Eunicida" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bellii">
<emphasis box="[1294,1383,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">P. bellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered as a widely distributed species since was recorded in the Northwest Atlantic Ocean, Grand Caribbean, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,249,1159,1185]" name="Vietnam" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, and the Persian Gulf. However, a recent morphological revision restricts the distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MNHN-AZ" baseAuthorityName="Audouin &amp; Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1282,1367,1159,1185]" class="Polychaeta" family="Eunicidae" genus="Paucibranchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Eunicida" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bellii">
<emphasis box="[1282,1367,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">P. bellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the Northeast Atlantic and West Mediterranean Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Molina-Acevedo, I. C." box="[689,947,1195,1221]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" pagination="1 - 125" refId="ref14193" refString="Molina-Acevedo, I. C. (2018) Morphological revision of the Subgroup 1 Fauchald, 1970 of Marphysa de Quatrefages, 1865 (Eunicidae: Polychaeta). Zootaxa, 4480 (1), 1 - 125. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4480.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Molina-Acevedo 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Some of these records were later described as a new species (
<taxonomicName authority="Molina-Acevedo, 2018" authorityName="Molina-Acevedo" authorityYear="2018" box="[368,904,1231,1257]" class="Polychaeta" family="Eunicidae" genus="Paucibranchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Eunicida" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="andresi">
<emphasis box="[368,629,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Paucibranchia andresi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Molina-Acevedo, I. C." box="[640,904,1231,1257]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" pagination="1 - 125" refId="ref14193" refString="Molina-Acevedo, I. C. (2018) Morphological revision of the Subgroup 1 Fauchald, 1970 of Marphysa de Quatrefages, 1865 (Eunicidae: Polychaeta). Zootaxa, 4480 (1), 1 - 125. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4480.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Molina-Acevedo, 2018</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[981,1143,1231,1257]" country="United States of America" name="Massachusetts" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Massachusetts</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1162,1223,1231,1257]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">USA</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Molina-Acevedo" authorityYear="2018" box="[1247,1370,1231,1256]" class="Polychaeta" family="Eunicidae" genus="Paucibranchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Eunicida" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="carrerai">
<emphasis box="[1247,1370,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">P. carrerai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,249,1267,1293]" name="Vietnam" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, and unnamed taxa 
<taxonomicName box="[476,705,1267,1293]" class="Polychaeta" family="Eunicidae" genus="Paucibranchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Eunicida" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undefined-1">
<emphasis box="[476,642,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="351">Paucibranchia</emphasis>
sp. 1
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Molina-Acevedo, I. C." box="[713,974,1267,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="351" pagination="1 - 125" refId="ref14193" refString="Molina-Acevedo, I. C. (2018) Morphological revision of the Subgroup 1 Fauchald, 1970 of Marphysa de Quatrefages, 1865 (Eunicidae: Polychaeta). Zootaxa, 4480 (1), 1 - 125. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4480.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Molina-Acevedo, 2018</bibRefCitation>
from the Gulf of Mexico), revealing the diversity hidden under the same name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
